This paper discusses a novel approach for conflict resolution in MVCC for in-memory databases, which is a topic related to database management systems (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a low overhead approach for summarizing transaction programs in the form of a dependency graph, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the performance bottleneck of the "abort and restart" approach, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
